Label: Paleopathological investigation
Definition: An investigation with the objective to assess one human skeleton for traces of pathological conditions as prescribed by the Phaleron Bioarchaeological Project research routine.

Label: Paleopathological observation
Definition: A planned process with the objective to collect data about an observed paleopathological condition.

Label: Observation of added bone
Definition: A planned process with the objective to collect data about an occurrence of abnormal bone addition.

Label: Observation of bone loss
Definition: A planned process with the objective to collect data about an occurrence of bone loss.

Label: Research contribution process
Definition: A planned process with the objective to contribute to some larger research process.
Participant Restriction: ('has participant' some (obo:NCBITaxon_9606 and ('bearer of' only phaleron-patho:ObserverRole)))

Label: Observer
Definition: An investigation agent role borne by a person which is realized in an investigation process.

Label: Data editor
Definition: An investigation agent role borne by a person which is realized in an investigation process.
